From bd2f26af42694131fb1e70a38b234a1b96798f69 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jeremy Andrews <athenian200@outlook.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 02:01:32 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] No Issue - Test patch for non-English users.

No idea if this is a viable/solid approach long-term or if there are
downsides, but this basically makes the build system honor CHCP on
Windows and pay attention to the console encoding rather than just
the system's ANSI codepage. Russian text appears correctly in the
build system with this. Even on non-Russian systems thanks to the
flexibility of this approach.

Has not been tested with many languages, or other OSes. Patch may
be put on the back burner due to more pressing Linux issues arising.
